  "notes": "Northern Catalan (Rossellonès/Septentrional). Spoken in Pyrénées-Orientales, France. Eastern block. Extreme unstressed vowel deletion (syncope) beyond standard Eastern Catalan schwa reduction. French phonological influence: uvular rhotic [ʁ] replacing traditional /r/, with /ɾ/ also realized as [ʁ] by many speakers. Final obstruent devoicing less categorical than in Central Catalan. Declining rapidly under French societal pressure.",
